  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 5.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Then",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Not merely temporal, as probably in ver. 13, but almost consequential, \"thereupon\"; so also ver. 15; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 2:7, 16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". John's preaching and manner of life were not without effect. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Went out",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐξεπορεύετο",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (similar in the parallels). Our Lord, when referring to this (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 11:7, 8, 9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), uses the commoner ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐξήλθατε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", merely indicating the crowds leaving for a while their present surroundings. The synoptists here point rather to the trouble involved and the distance traversed (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 6:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " with 12). The singular is used (as often in the Hebrew) because the writer's first thought was of Jerusalem; the other parts were added as an afterthought. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "All",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 8:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " from all parts and in large numbers. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Judaea",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Strictly speaking, this would, of course, include part of the next expression, but the reference here is especially to the hill-country. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And all the region round about Jordan",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the inhabitants of the Ghor, the Jordan valley. They presumably came from either side of the river. \"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Strabo",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", concerning the plain bordering on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Jordan",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", hath these words: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "It is a place of an hundred furlongs",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "all well watered",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "and full of dwellings\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "  (John Lightfoot, 'Her. Heb.'). Matthew 3:5",
        "children": []
      }
